Dr olaru met all my expectations! She has been the only gynecologist I will see again for future check ups!  I have been through many over the past 30 years!
She was knowledgeable, explained all ,  her dedication to her work was felt in a caring manner!
Beatrice Delmonico

originalText.text: Dr. Olaru is phenomenal! She was able to explain my symptoms and procedures thoroughly. However, I can't say the same about my experience with her colleague, Dr. Shay; he undermined what Dr. Olaru said and dismissed my concerns during the hysteroscopy Dr. Olaru requested. Furthermore, Dr. Shay hadn't read my file before the hysteroscopy and didn't know who my ob-gyn was. The entire experience with him left me feeling confused and enfeebled.

originalText.text:
Unfortunately, after years of coming to this doctor the experience has become intolerable due to her administrative, office support staff. Consistent 1-2hour wait times set aside, when facing a diagnosis, waiting for scripts or wanting information/bare bones info post appointments or test results, I am met with an inability to answer questions, promises to be called back or contacted by nurses that never do, information and results that are not uploaded to my patient portal in a timely fashion (sometimes never even making it there), the list goes on. Once or twice I’ve had positive test results I was never contacted about and only found out the next time I visited for my routine check up!

The doctor herself is very knowledgeable and nice so if you are looking for an average annual or biannual OBGYN experience and lucky enough to never need any further assistance you’re probably fine to come here. But should you ever come to this doctor with a concern, issue or abnormal result, LOOK ELSEWHERE. I have only ever been left hanging, confused and even more concerned than before I came.

originalText.text: I recently started seeing Dr. Olaru, who I really love. I came to her from a recommendation from a friend. She's always been so lovely, honest and is providing a lot of helpful guidance in the beginning of my pregnancy. Sometimes she gives me advice I don't want to hear (like telling me I have to rest in my first Trimester) but that's a good doctor. I would recommend her to anyone and I actually go to her office all the way from Brooklyn to see her, meaning she's worth the longer commute.

originalText.text: Dr. Olaru was incredible at listening to my concerns and telling me what to expect during our first visit together. The front desk staff was lovely and Andrea, the nurse, was incredibly lovely. I've had bad experiences with doctors since changing my insurance but Dr. Olaru and her staff are definitely a practice I'm comfortable sticking with!
